Cypress Screenshot functionality is: 
https://www.npmjs.com/package/cypress-plugin-snapshots 

Installation All Commands till now:--------------------
apt-get install libgtk2.0-0 libgtk-3-0 libgbm-dev libnotify-dev libgconf-2-4 libnss3 libxss1 libasound2 libxtst6 xauth xvfb
npm install cypress --save-dev
$(npm bin)/cypress open


Mochawesome installation------------------------------------
npm install --save-dev mochawesome
npm install mochawesome-merge --save-dev
npm install -g mochawesome-report-generator


Run commands in Terminal for Cypress:
- Code to run Cypress:  ./node_modules/.bin/cypress open
- Headless mode run: ./node_modules/.bin/cypress run
- To run for the Cypress dashboard: ./node_modules/.bin/cypress run --record --key 3554230a-fdea-4f74-a835-63b2cfdf0b28


For Reports:
./node_modules/.bin/cypress run --spec cypress/integration/[FOLDER_NAME]/[FILE_NAME OR *].js --browser chrome

For test suite:
./node_modules/.bin/cypress run --spec cypress/integration/final_code/*.js --browser chrome

Npm merge to create a collective JSON report
Npm merge_report (merge_report is the variable name set in package.json) to create an HTML version of the Reports



